- Male R, female W: genotype RW (eyes white)
- Male W, female R: genotype WR (eyes white)
- Male W, female W: genotype WW (eyes white)

Eyes look white for genotypes RW, WR, and WW, which occur in three out of four cases. Thus, the probability of white eyes is 3/4.

The event of having two white alleles (WW) occurs in one out of four cases, and this also results in white eyes.

The conditional probability of having two white alleles given white eyes is the probability of WW divided by the probability of white eyes: (1/4) / (3/4) = 1/3.

