* RESPONSE 1 *
**************
The solution calculates the probability \(P(52.761 \leq \bar{X} \leq 54.453)\) for the sample mean \(\bar{X}\) using the Central Limit Theorem. The standard error is \(\sigma_{\bar{X}} = \frac{5.8}{\sqrt{47}} \approx 0.8457\). The z-scores are computed as \(z_{\text{lower}} \approx -1.500\) and \(z_{\text{upper}} \approx 0.500\). The probability \(P(-1.500 \leq Z \leq 0.500)\) is found using the standard normal distribution, resulting in \(0.6915 - 0.0668 = 0.6247\).

The final answer is a probability and is unitless.

The final answer is $0.6247$.
